entries.title: U.S., Israel Send Message to Iran With Biggest-Ever Military Exercises
entries.description: More than 180,000 pounds of live munitions were fired, and thousands of personnel took part in the exercise.

entries.title: Biden Extends Protections for Hong Kong Residents in U.S.
entries.description: Hong Kongers will be permitted to stay for at least two years even if their visas expire, as China cracks down on political dissent in the city.

entries.title: Roman Abramovich's Long-Shot Effort to Save Ukraine, His Reputation and His Fortune
entries.description: The Russian oligarch has thrown himself into a quest to help stop the war and salvage his reputation in the West. Now his chances to be a middleman for peace are falling, while the pressure on his assets is increasing.

entries.title: Chinese Consumers Embrace Life Free From Zero-Covid Controls
entries.description: Chinese travelers flooded tourism hotspots at home and booked more trips abroad halfway through the first long public holiday since Beijing ended zero-Covid controls.

entries.title: New U.S. Base on Guam Is Aimed at Deterring China
entries.description: The base on Guam, the first new one for the Marines since 1952, will eventually house 5,000 troops.

entries.title: U.S. Pressures Turkey Over Russian Flights
entries.description: U.S. officials are leaning on Turkey to stop Russian airlines from flying American-made airplanes to and from the country, said officials familiar with the talks.

entries.title: Israeli Raid in West Bank Leaves Nine Palestinians Dead
entries.description: A firefight between militants and Israeli security forces during an Israeli raid in the West Bank left nine Palestinians dead, according to Palestinian health officials.

entries.title: Ukraine Under New Missile Barrage as Russia Warns West About Tank Pledges
entries.description: Explosions rocked Kyiv, while officials in Moscow said the latest promises of Western military aid would escalate the conflict.
